								HISD Covid 19 Update
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_7_title"><p>
								Attention HISD Parents/Guardians:<br>Since we are anticipating word from Governor Abbott regarding the public school year later on this week, we do not have a formal update for you.  However, we would like an update from you. <br>Please let us know how the at-home learning opportunities provided by Hallettsville ISD are going by answering this short survey. We look forward to learning how we can help you! <br><br>https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/AtHomeLearningSurvey<br><br><br>Thank you!
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_8" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_8_title">
		<a href="https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/HISDMeals">
								Reminder: Hallettsville ISD Meal Packet Sign Up
							</a>
						</h1>
					</header><section class="summary cf" itemprop="description" aria-labelledby="hp_news_article_8_title"><p>
								On our March 16th Covid-19 Survey to the community, we asked about nutritional needs for HISD students.<br>HISD will be starting meal service on Thursday, March 26th.<br>Students will receive lunch for the current day and breakfast for the next morning.<br>This service is available for ANY CHILD (AGE 1 - 12TH GRADE)<br>The pickup location will be in the parking lot behind the High School.<br>The pickup time is 10:30 AM – 12:30 PM (Monday – Friday).<br>At pickup, you will have to provide the names of the children receiving meals. Children DO NOT have to be present in cars to receive a meal package.<br>HISD is collaborating with Region 3 Education Service Center and the Texas Department of Agriculture to provide these meals at NO CHARGE.<br><br>Please call or email Roberta Jurena before 9 AM if you have signed up for a meal and do not need it for that day. (361-798-2242 ext 380 or rjurena@hisdbrahmas.org)<br><br>https://www.surveymonkey.com/r/HISDMeals
							</p>
						</section></article><article id="hp_news_article_9" class="cf" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"><header class="cf"><h1 class="title" itemprop="name headline" id="hp_news_article_9_title">
